ZH: 这个系统的规定过于僵化，需要进行更新。
EN: The regulations of this system are too rigid and need to be updated.

ZH: 这个老板总是僵化地坚持自己的意见，不肯接受别人的建议。
EN: The boss always rigidly sticks to his own opinions and refuses to accept other people's suggestions.

ZH: 政府的决策机制已经非常僵化，难以适应快速变化的情况。
EN: The government's decision-making mechanism has become very rigid and cannot adapt to rapid changes.

ZH: 这家公司的管理体制太过僵化，员工们感到无法发挥自己的创造力。
EN: The management system of this company is too rigid, and employees feel unable to unleash their creativity.

ZH: 这个学校的教学方法已经僵化多年，需要进行改革。
EN: The teaching methods of this school have been rigid for many years and need reform.

ZH: 经常锻炼可以帮助身体避免僵化。
EN: Regular exercise can help prevent the body from becoming stiff.

ZH: 长时间固定的姿势会导致身体的僵化。
EN: Prolonged sitting in the same position can cause the body to become stiff.

ZH: 他的观点已经很久没有更新了，有点僵化。
EN: His opinions have not been updated for a long time and are a bit rigid.

ZH: 工作中不要过于僵化，应该灵活处理各种问题。
EN: Do not be too rigid at work, be flexible in dealing with various issues.

