EN: In the ever-changing market, companies cannot rigidly stick to their original business models.

ZH: 僵化的思维会限制个人的发展。
EN: Rigid thinking can limit personal development.

ZH: 过度的管制和规定会导致企业僵化、创新力受到抑制。
EN: Excessive regulations and rules can lead to the rigidity of enterprises and inhibit innovation.

ZH: 学生们应该避免僵化地死记硬背，应该灵活运用所学知识。
EN: Students should avoid rigidly memorizing and should instead flexibly apply the knowledge they have learned.

ZH: 企业要想在激烈的竞争中生存，就必须打破僵化的体制。
EN: In order to survive in fierce competition, companies must break free from rigid systems.

